# Eklogi API Documentation
Sample api documentation for sample project.

# Allowed HTTPs requests:
<pre>
GET     : Get a resource or list of resources
</pre>

# Possible User Responses:
- 200 `OK` - the request was successful (some API calls may return 201 instead).
- 204 `No Content` - the request was successful but there is no representation to return (i.e. the response is empty).
- 400 `Bad Request` - the request could not be understood or was missing required parameters.
- 405 `Method Not Allowed` - requested method is not supported for resource.

# Group Members
Represents the details of politicians.

---
**Member attributes:**

- id `(String)` : unique identifier. 
- name `(String)` : Name of member.
- party `(String)` : Party which member is part of.
- state `(String)` : State member represents.
- chamber `(String)` : Which chamber of congress member is part of.

---
## Member Collection [people]
### List all members [GET]
Retrieve all members of current congress

+ curl "https://api.eklogi.me/people/"

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        [
            {
                "id": "K000388",
                "name": "Trent Kelly",
                "party": "Republican",
                "state": "MS"
                "chamber": "House"
            },
            {
                "id": "Y000064",
                "name": "Tod Young",
                "party": "Republican",
                "state": "IN"
                "chamber": "Senate"
            },
            {
                "id": "C001113",
                "name": "Catherine Cortez Masto",
                "party": "Democrat",
                "state": "NV"
                "chamber": "Senate"
            }
        ...
        ]


## Chamber Collection [people/{chamber}]
### List all members from a chamber [Get]
Returns all members from a chamber, which can be either the house or senate.

+ Parameters
    + chamber (required) ... House or senate

+ curl "https://api.eklogi.me/people/senate/"

+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body
        [
            {
                "id": "C001113",
                "name": "Catherine Cortez Masto",
                "party": "Democrat",
                "state": "NV"
                "chamber": "Senate"
            },
        ...
        ]

+ Response 400 (application/json)

        {
            "error": "no such chamber"
        }

## Single Member [people/{chamber}/{id}.json]
### Retrieve A Single Member [Get]
Return a specific member 
+ Parameters
    + chamber (required) ... House or senate
    + id (required) ... member's Id
    
+ curl "https://api.eklogi.me/senate/C001113.json"

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
                "id": "C001113",
                "name": "Catherine Cortez Masto",
                "party": "Democrat",
                "state": "NV"
                "chamber": "Senate"
        }

+ curl "https://api.eklogi.me/people/house/K000388.json"

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
                "id": "K000388",
                "name": "Trent Kelly",
                "party": "Republican",
                "state": "MS"
                "chamber": "House"
        }

